1
00:00:16,590 --> 00:00:18,240
Wanna stop by the store?

2
00:00:18,240 --> 00:00:21,040
- I know it's cold, but ice cream would...
- Ouji.

3
00:00:22,570 --> 00:00:27,020
I want to have sex with you.

4
00:00:41,220 --> 00:00:42,860
Erm...

5
00:00:47,200 --> 00:00:48,340
Oreo.

6
00:00:48,340 --> 00:00:49,810
Come here, boy!

7
00:00:49,810 --> 00:00:50,940
Sorry to bother.

8
00:00:50,940 --> 00:00:52,960
- It's fine.
- No worries.

9
00:01:00,110 --> 00:01:04,100
Let's just get home, yeah?

10
00:01:05,610 --> 00:01:08,280
Okay. Yeah.

11
00:01:17,260 --> 00:01:19,420
<i>Dragging me by the arm?</i>

12
00:01:35,250 --> 00:01:40,650
<i>Can it be? Can I expect something tonight?</i>

13
00:01:40,650 --> 00:01:42,720
Should we open a bottle?

14
00:01:45,030 --> 00:01:48,280
- What's up?
- How do you make tea?

15
00:01:48,280 --> 00:01:50,080
Tea?

16
00:01:50,080 --> 00:01:53,970
First, you have to brew the water.

17
00:01:53,970 --> 00:01:56,770
Right. The water.

18
00:01:59,030 --> 00:02:00,990
Tea?

19
00:02:09,700 --> 00:02:17,030
Am I... being rejected right now?

20
00:02:17,690 --> 00:02:19,390
Listen.

21
00:02:21,560 --> 00:02:24,560
I was equally as happy, you know?

22
00:02:27,420 --> 00:02:30,540
To hug you and all.

23
00:02:33,770 --> 00:02:37,610
I just felt awkward saying it.

24
00:02:40,720 --> 00:02:42,970
The thing is...

25
00:02:46,940 --> 00:02:50,760
I actually love you, Haru.

26
00:02:54,330 --> 00:03:00,910
I know we married on the fly,
and got the order all wrong, but...

27
00:03:11,410 --> 00:03:12,890
Haru?

28
00:03:29,710 --> 00:03:31,620
I'm so relieved.

29
00:03:35,980 --> 00:03:37,810
I feel so happy right now.

30
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:41,620
I...

31
00:03:42,950 --> 00:03:46,960
I've been waiting to hear those words...

32
00:03:49,210 --> 00:03:52,900
All this time.

33
00:03:57,670 --> 00:04:02,690
Ouji, I...

34
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:45,180
I love you, too.

35
00:05:21,310 --> 00:05:22,990
I'm sorry.

36
00:06:23,190 --> 00:06:27,310
[Episode 5]

37
00:06:37,750 --> 00:06:40,270
[Heading out to a meeting]

38
00:06:43,030 --> 00:06:47,770
Their mini album will be released
after the concert.

39
00:06:47,770 --> 00:06:51,920
We'll decide the number of songs
at a later date.

40
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:53,670
As for next year's agenda...

41
00:07:08,800 --> 00:07:12,420
Marriage ain't so easy after all, right?

42
00:07:12,420 --> 00:07:13,600
Huh?

43
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:16,330
At least, that's what your face is saying.

44
00:07:16,330 --> 00:07:18,010
What's that supposed to mean?

45
00:07:18,010 --> 00:07:19,730
Quit making assumptions.

46
00:07:19,730 --> 00:07:24,260
On the brink of a divorce
after you were caught cheating?

47
00:07:24,260 --> 00:07:25,440
Hell no.

48
00:07:25,440 --> 00:07:27,010
Yeah, I don't think that's it.

49
00:07:27,010 --> 00:07:29,920
Ouji's changed ever since he married Haru.

50
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:31,700
It's like he's mellowed out.

51
00:07:31,700 --> 00:07:33,880
That'll help improve our image.

52
00:07:33,880 --> 00:07:37,760
Right? Coincidence or not, I'll take it.

53
00:07:37,760 --> 00:07:41,420
Haru's got a compelling power like that.

54
00:07:41,420 --> 00:07:42,860
I know.

55
00:07:42,860 --> 00:07:46,390
Huh, you're actually serious about her.

56
00:07:46,390 --> 00:07:48,240
I said, quit making assumptions.

57
00:07:48,240 --> 00:07:50,230
We have to. You won't tell us a thing,

58
00:07:50,230 --> 00:07:52,300
even after two decades of playing together.

59
00:07:52,300 --> 00:07:56,670
Then you two know Haru as well as I do.

60
00:07:56,670 --> 00:07:59,390
You're asking about our thoughts on Haru?

61
00:07:59,390 --> 00:08:03,060
Well, I remember she'd wait for us
after shows and before recordings.

62
00:08:03,060 --> 00:08:06,080
She was a groupie, or practically a stalk...

63
00:08:06,080 --> 00:08:07,810
Haru isn't...

64
00:08:08,790 --> 00:08:10,530
She isn't like that.

65
00:08:14,260 --> 00:08:19,470
We're considering solo activities as well.

66
00:08:19,470 --> 00:08:21,460
And you, Tanaka?

67
00:08:24,260 --> 00:08:25,710
Ouji.

68
00:08:25,710 --> 00:08:28,660
I think that individual
works for a tabloid magazine.

69
00:08:28,660 --> 00:08:29,800
I've seen them around before.

70
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:33,330
Seriously? What a pain.

71
00:08:33,330 --> 00:08:35,090
Guess the party's over.

72
00:08:40,130 --> 00:08:44,240
Hamburger steaks, huh? My favorite.

73
00:08:49,500 --> 00:08:51,830
Holy cow, that's good.

74
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:58,210
Let's just get married.

75
00:08:59,270 --> 00:09:01,490
WHAT?

76
00:09:04,460 --> 00:09:07,440
That hurts... Why?

77
00:09:07,440 --> 00:09:09,520
Wait, this is real?

78
00:09:09,520 --> 00:09:12,420
Of course it's real.

79
00:09:18,100 --> 00:09:21,980
Hey, no more crying, okay?

80
00:09:23,240 --> 00:09:24,890
Ow, ouch.

81
00:09:26,960 --> 00:09:28,580
Welcome back!

82
00:09:29,470 --> 00:09:31,060
I'm home.

83
00:09:33,980 --> 00:09:36,820
Good night! Sweet dreams!

84
00:09:53,010 --> 00:09:57,950
I do actually love her.

85
00:09:59,050 --> 00:10:02,100
Your expression says otherwise.

86
00:10:02,100 --> 00:10:05,500
- Huh?
- Yeah, why the dissatisfied look?

87
00:10:05,500 --> 00:10:10,110
I'm not dissatisfied, it's just...

88
00:10:10,110 --> 00:10:11,940
I love her.

89
00:10:12,630 --> 00:10:15,400
Which is exactly why it's not so simple.

90
00:10:16,820 --> 00:10:21,640
Ouji. I think you're overthinking it.

91
00:10:21,640 --> 00:10:26,630
This is your first crush,
and your first marriage.

92
00:10:26,630 --> 00:10:30,790
Of course you're confused.

93
00:10:30,790 --> 00:10:35,820
- Well...
- If you love her, take it a step at a time.

94
00:10:37,870 --> 00:10:41,480
If only I could.

95
00:10:41,480 --> 00:10:45,050
What, so you just wanted to brag?

96
00:10:45,050 --> 00:10:47,660
Man, I want to get married, too.

97
00:10:47,660 --> 00:10:50,180
Your first step is to quit four-timing.
[Keiko Kotani]

98
00:10:50,180 --> 00:10:52,620
I'm serious about all of them!
[Can we meet later today?]

99
00:10:52,620 --> 00:10:56,170
Trash. You utter scumbag.

100
00:11:03,640 --> 00:11:06,430
- Haru, are you hungry?
- Huh?

101
00:11:06,430 --> 00:11:07,680
Was my stomach growling?

102
00:11:07,680 --> 00:11:11,980
No, but there's a taco rice truck out front.
How about it?

103
00:11:11,980 --> 00:11:14,790
Sorry, but I'm grabbing lunch
with some friends today.

104
00:11:14,790 --> 00:11:16,960
Ah, I see.

105
00:11:16,960 --> 00:11:19,610
I'm free to grab a quick coffee, though.

106
00:11:19,610 --> 00:11:24,050
I finished writing my draft early today.

107
00:11:24,050 --> 00:11:26,100
Inspiration's flowing?

108
00:11:26,100 --> 00:11:31,110
Yeah. I overcame a hurdle of some sort.

109
00:11:33,250 --> 00:11:35,600
Oh? That's good to hear.

110
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:37,550
Should we get going?

111
00:11:37,550 --> 00:11:39,740
No, let's shelve it for another day.

112
00:11:39,740 --> 00:11:42,260
I'd rather try it out with you.

113
00:11:42,260 --> 00:11:43,900
If you insist.

114
00:11:45,140 --> 00:11:49,840
Didn't realize you were
such a fan of taco rice.

115
00:11:49,840 --> 00:11:51,340
You could say that.

116
00:11:51,340 --> 00:11:53,110
Wow.

117
00:12:06,400 --> 00:12:10,200
[Ouji]

118
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:12,390
<i>Sorry, I'll be late tonight.</i>

119
00:12:19,130 --> 00:12:23,440
Haru. It's a bit creepy seeing you
grinning in the streets like that.

120
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:27,960
<i>Roger!</i>

121
00:12:39,500 --> 00:12:41,780
- Fuyumi!
- There you are!

122
00:12:41,780 --> 00:12:43,700
Thanks for waiting.

123
00:12:46,320 --> 00:12:49,650
Drinking while the sun's still up?

124
00:12:49,650 --> 00:12:52,870
Yup. I already finished work for the day.

125
00:12:52,870 --> 00:12:57,350
Wait, that can't be the only reason
you're beaming.

126
00:12:57,350 --> 00:12:59,140
Haru, you haven't told her yet?

127
00:12:59,140 --> 00:13:03,050
I thought she'd be a bit exasperated,
hearing me gloat.

128
00:13:03,050 --> 00:13:04,660
Already am.

129
00:13:04,660 --> 00:13:06,180
Thought so.

130
00:13:06,900 --> 00:13:10,030
Okay, here me out.

131
00:13:12,340 --> 00:13:14,630
- A hug...
- A confession...

132
00:13:14,630 --> 00:13:17,160
And then another hug?

133
00:13:17,160 --> 00:13:19,030
Yup.

134
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:23,680
Cheers!

135
00:13:25,090 --> 00:13:29,010
Your drink must taste all the sweeter, Haru.

136
00:13:29,010 --> 00:13:33,600
Such pure love at your age... Savor it!

137
00:13:33,600 --> 00:13:38,220
Thank you two for always listening.

138
00:13:38,220 --> 00:13:41,490
Then I bet you're raring to go home tonight?

139
00:13:41,490 --> 00:13:45,190
No, Ouji says work is keeping him late today.

140
00:13:45,190 --> 00:13:47,930
Gosh, I'm a bit miffed after all!

141
00:13:47,930 --> 00:13:52,820
I know we did things in the wrong order.

142
00:13:52,820 --> 00:13:55,690
But now that we've reaffirmed our feelings,

143
00:13:55,690 --> 00:13:57,460
I feel absolutely fulfilled.

144
00:13:57,460 --> 00:14:01,310
I suppose order doesn't matter after all.

145
00:14:01,310 --> 00:14:03,780
Sure, he still lacks a sex drive.

146
00:14:03,780 --> 00:14:07,170
But it doesn't seem like
such an obstacle anymore.

147
00:14:07,170 --> 00:14:10,410
We'll overcome that wall, together.

148
00:14:10,410 --> 00:14:13,600
You're grinning wide. Cute!

149
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:21,760
I'm sure Akina's thinking love is pointless
without the sex, though.

150
00:14:21,760 --> 00:14:26,180
No, I think it's a wonderful development.

151
00:14:26,180 --> 00:14:29,810
- What?
- If you're certain he loves you,

152
00:14:29,810 --> 00:14:34,620
then maybe you can hold off on sex after all.

153
00:14:34,620 --> 00:14:37,300
Huh? Who are you?

154
00:14:37,300 --> 00:14:39,080
What did you to do our Akina?

155
00:14:39,080 --> 00:14:44,560
Let's just say I met someone
who changed my mind.

156
00:14:44,560 --> 00:14:46,140
What?

157
00:14:46,140 --> 00:14:48,860
- A platonic love?
- Wow...

158
00:14:48,860 --> 00:14:51,240
I didn't realize platonic feelings
were contagious.

159
00:14:51,240 --> 00:14:54,930
No, I don't feel a platonic love for him.

160
00:14:54,930 --> 00:14:58,240
And we've done everything but go all the way.

161
00:14:58,240 --> 00:15:01,250
- Erotic as that may sound.
- Woah.

162
00:15:01,250 --> 00:15:08,840
Anyway, I sort of understand how you felt
when you first met Ouji.

163
00:15:11,490 --> 00:15:15,930
<i>Let us both enjoy our time together.</i>

164
00:15:15,930 --> 00:15:20,170
<i>He made me think, "he's the one"...</i>

165
00:15:20,170 --> 00:15:22,620
Type of relationship be damned.

166
00:15:23,210 --> 00:15:25,110
I see.

167
00:15:25,110 --> 00:15:27,730
To think even Akina would find someone.

168
00:15:27,730 --> 00:15:29,610
So what's he like?

169
00:15:29,610 --> 00:15:31,900
Is he a foreign dude?

170
00:15:31,900 --> 00:15:34,080
His face sort of looks like it.

171
00:15:34,080 --> 00:15:36,450
He kinda gives "K-pop idol" vibes...

172
00:15:36,450 --> 00:15:38,220
No, a boxer.

173
00:15:38,220 --> 00:15:39,850
You're confusing us.

174
00:15:39,850 --> 00:15:43,450
More importantly,
his mannerisms are to die for!

175
00:15:43,450 --> 00:15:46,320
He's usually the courteous type, except...

176
00:15:46,320 --> 00:15:49,760
What's the matter, Akina?

177
00:15:56,060 --> 00:15:58,750
I hate being the only one who's feeling it.

178
00:15:59,460 --> 00:16:02,840
I want to make you feel good, too.

179
00:16:02,840 --> 00:16:07,300
- Huh?
- We're allowed to go halfway, right?

180
00:16:07,300 --> 00:16:09,760
I'm confident in my skills.

181
00:16:12,390 --> 00:16:18,350
I'd be tempted to stay,
so that'll have to be a "nope" from me.

182
00:16:19,720 --> 00:16:22,600
What? What is it?

183
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:24,280
Give us an example.

184
00:16:24,280 --> 00:16:27,420
He'll drop the courtesy, without warning.

185
00:16:27,420 --> 00:16:29,970
Why is that so effective?

186
00:16:29,970 --> 00:16:31,680
I get it!

187
00:16:31,680 --> 00:16:32,810
You do, Fuyumi?

188
00:16:32,810 --> 00:16:37,530
I love getting a glimpse
of their true colors.

189
00:16:37,530 --> 00:16:40,650
- It makes my heart squeeze!
- I'm the opposite.

190
00:16:40,650 --> 00:16:43,190
I love the professionalism
of keeping an appropriate distance.

191
00:16:43,190 --> 00:16:45,070
"Professionalism"?

192
00:16:45,070 --> 00:16:48,550
- It's just an example.
- Nicknames are great, too.

193
00:16:48,550 --> 00:16:54,560
Going from "hey you",
to a cute nickname? It's the best!

194
00:16:54,560 --> 00:16:56,190
Sounds like a player. Sorry, can't relate.

195
00:16:56,190 --> 00:16:58,920
Don't get rational on me now.

196
00:16:58,920 --> 00:17:03,960
Going from "Ms." to first name basis
is what gets me.

197
00:17:03,960 --> 00:17:08,040
Name-calling in bed is pretty great, too.

198
00:17:10,150 --> 00:17:14,420
Our preferences are all over the place,

199
00:17:14,420 --> 00:17:19,350
but we're ultimately charmed
by these people, huh?

200
00:17:19,350 --> 00:17:24,560
Personally, I'm fulfilled
just hearing your stories.

201
00:17:24,560 --> 00:17:26,890
Do our stories entertain you?

202
00:17:26,890 --> 00:17:30,160
Yes, they're almost too stimulating.

203
00:17:33,610 --> 00:17:35,550
Jeez...

204
00:17:37,710 --> 00:17:39,580
[An article next week will report a scandal]

205
00:17:39,580 --> 00:17:41,340
[between a stage play actor and our staff]

206
00:17:42,910 --> 00:17:44,700
What happened?

207
00:17:44,700 --> 00:17:46,200
Fuyumi?

208
00:17:46,200 --> 00:17:47,840
Fuyumi?

209
00:17:48,960 --> 00:17:51,670
[Apparently, his partner's a makeup artist]

210
00:17:54,400 --> 00:17:55,580
[An article next week will report a scandal]

211
00:17:55,580 --> 00:17:56,870
[between a stage play actor and our staff]

212
00:18:00,530 --> 00:18:02,620
Is everything okay?

213
00:18:07,160 --> 00:18:11,320
Someone at the elementary school
was afflicted with food poisoning.

214
00:18:11,320 --> 00:18:14,540
I-I'm sure Chizuka is fine, but...

215
00:18:14,540 --> 00:18:17,920
I'm sorry. I need to go hear the details.

216
00:18:17,920 --> 00:18:19,750
- Okay.
- Don't worry about paying.

217
00:18:19,750 --> 00:18:21,530
- Hurry.
- Sorry, thank you.

218
00:18:21,530 --> 00:18:23,190
Take care!

219
00:18:46,650 --> 00:18:48,000
[Shota]

220
00:18:56,660 --> 00:18:59,450
[Shota]
[Please give me a call]

221
00:18:59,450 --> 00:19:00,940
[Have you heard?]
[About the article]

222
00:19:03,710 --> 00:19:05,930
I shouldn't leave any evidence.

223
00:19:07,860 --> 00:19:10,110
No, it's too late now.

224
00:19:10,110 --> 00:19:11,040
[Delete message]

225
00:19:11,040 --> 00:19:13,320
[Shota]

226
00:19:14,330 --> 00:19:15,760
Shota?

227
00:19:15,760 --> 00:19:17,780
<i>Fuyumi...</i>

228
00:19:17,780 --> 00:19:20,980
Did you hear the news? About the article.

229
00:19:20,980 --> 00:19:26,240
I did. An affair. Could it be...

230
00:19:26,240 --> 00:19:28,430
I wonder how we were found out.

231
00:19:28,430 --> 00:19:29,670
What?

232
00:19:29,670 --> 00:19:33,860
We always met at my place, right?

233
00:19:33,860 --> 00:19:36,100
<i>We never went in at the same time, too.</i>

234
00:19:36,100 --> 00:19:39,580
And I made sure to keep
an appropriate distance at work.

235
00:19:39,580 --> 00:19:42,080
- That might be it.
- Huh?

236
00:19:43,300 --> 00:19:46,710
We may have acted too close.

237
00:19:47,560 --> 00:19:50,980
What should I do?

238
00:19:51,700 --> 00:19:53,650
I'm sorry.

239
00:19:54,650 --> 00:19:56,520
<i>Shota, I...</i>

240
00:19:58,880 --> 00:20:00,590
<i>I'm so sorry.</i>

241
00:20:01,570 --> 00:20:03,960
Don't apologize, Fuyumi.

242
00:20:05,650 --> 00:20:09,150
I'm the one who fell for you first.

243
00:20:09,150 --> 00:20:12,040
But I'm the adult. I work backstage.

244
00:20:12,040 --> 00:20:15,760
No more of that, okay?

245
00:20:17,440 --> 00:20:19,350
I want you to see me as your equal.

246
00:20:21,700 --> 00:20:23,930
If the article is published,

247
00:20:25,190 --> 00:20:30,560
I'll say I insisted on pursuing something.

248
00:20:31,460 --> 00:20:33,680
Tell them you couldn't turn me down.

249
00:20:33,680 --> 00:20:35,020
Why would you...

250
00:20:35,020 --> 00:20:36,960
Because I want to protect you.

251
00:20:38,870 --> 00:20:40,990
Though I may be younger,

252
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:44,900
I'm a man, first and foremost.

253
00:20:52,950 --> 00:20:55,530
My manager's calling.

254
00:20:55,530 --> 00:21:00,040
I'll text again if I learn something new.

255
00:21:01,040 --> 00:21:02,520
Okay.

256
00:21:13,650 --> 00:21:15,460
<i>I'm sorry I got worked up.</i>

257
00:21:15,460 --> 00:21:20,620
<i>Chizuka was fine, as are the other kids.</i>

258
00:21:20,620 --> 00:21:22,480
Thank goodness.

259
00:21:22,480 --> 00:21:26,800
Seriously, she looked so worried
when she left.

260
00:21:27,580 --> 00:21:30,690
She really is a mother, isn't she?

261
00:21:30,690 --> 00:21:32,520
She sure is.

262
00:21:32,520 --> 00:21:36,470
Alright. Now that we know Chizuka's okay,

263
00:21:36,470 --> 00:21:39,220
how about we go for karaoke?

264
00:21:39,220 --> 00:21:42,260
I've had enough secondhand happiness
for the day.

265
00:21:42,260 --> 00:21:43,890
Besides, I have plans.

266
00:21:43,890 --> 00:21:47,410
But I still have lots to share...

267
00:21:48,680 --> 00:21:50,140
Wait, is it a date?

268
00:21:50,140 --> 00:21:51,900
With Mr. Eros?

269
00:21:51,900 --> 00:21:55,040
You could say that.

270
00:21:56,820 --> 00:21:59,850
You're poking fun at me like an old man.

271
00:22:06,140 --> 00:22:09,370
<i>If we've got extra time afterwards,
care to join me for a drink?</i>

272
00:22:12,290 --> 00:22:15,940
<i>Sounds good. But will we have extra time?</i>

273
00:22:15,940 --> 00:22:18,640
<i>So long as I don't feel too good.</i>

274
00:22:19,780 --> 00:22:21,710
<i>Then it seems we'll have no time after all.</i>

275
00:22:24,400 --> 00:22:26,030
Confident, isn't he?

276
00:22:42,770 --> 00:22:44,240
Huh?

277
00:23:08,570 --> 00:23:11,410
[Heading out to a meeting]

278
00:23:14,800 --> 00:23:16,430
Welcome home!

279
00:23:19,950 --> 00:23:21,760
Ouji?

280
00:23:21,760 --> 00:23:24,550
What's wrong?

281
00:23:25,230 --> 00:23:26,750
Haru.

282
00:23:29,670 --> 00:23:31,070
I'm sorry.

283
00:23:36,070 --> 00:23:38,670
- Ouji?
- Let's break up.

284
00:24:40,940 --> 00:24:48,970
[Preview]
